<h4>Payment Policy</h4>
<div>OIG has a long history involving prescription drug payment policy, including a prominent role in the complete overhaul of the Part B reimbursement methodology via the Medicare Modernization Act. Our work in this area has been credited with billions in savings to the Federal government.  In recent years we have focused on the differences in payment levels between Part D and Medicaid, additional methods to decrease drug expenditures in Part B, the effectiveness of Medicaid's rebate collection efforts, and manufacturer reporting of drug pricing data. </div>

